SIMPLE: presently
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presently
<hw>Pres"ent*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>At
present; at this time; now.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The towns and forts you <qex>presently</qex> have.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At once; without delay; forthwith; also, less
definitely, soon; shortly; before long; after a little while; by and
by.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>presently</qex> the fig tree withered away.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xxi. 19.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>With actual presence; actually .</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His precious body and blood <qex>presently three</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Gardiner.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presentment</ent>⟦br⟧
